From: nix-wasm <eric@codebutler.com>
Date: Thu, 25 Jun 2026 00:00:00 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] virtio_wasm: register a virtio-console device (VIRTIO_ID_CONSOLE)

Register a virtio-console device on the wasm virtio transport so the
stock mainline virtio-console driver (drivers/char/virtio_console.c,
CONFIG_VIRTIO_CONSOLE) can carry a guest TTY/console, riding the same
virtio_wasm carrier the 9P / blk / net devices already use. This is the
console edition of the "everything is a virtio device" consolidation
(issue #10, option 2): the guest gains a standard virtualized-Linux
console path (stock hvc-over-virtio) ALONGSIDE the existing bespoke
hvc_wasm backend, so the two can be A/B'd before hvc_wasm is retired in a
later change. This patch ADDS the virtio-console path; it does NOT remove
hvc_wasm (patches 0002/0003) — that is a separate follow-up gated on
boot-validating virtio-console.

SINGLE PORT (no VIRTIO_CONSOLE_F_MULTIPORT): mainline virtio_console
binds a port to a (receiveq, transmitq) vq pair; a featureless device
gets exactly ONE port (port 0) which the driver wires to hvc as a console
line — vq[0] = receiveq (host->guest input), vq[1] = transmitq
(guest->host output). That is the hvc-equivalent of one console, which is
all this path needs to A/B against hvc0. We deliberately offer NO feature
bits: VIRTIO_CONSOLE_F_SIZE (cols/rows in config space) is unused (the
TIOCSWINSZ path stays on hvc_wasm's wasm_driver_hvc_winsize for now), and
VIRTIO_CONSOLE_F_MULTIPORT (the control vq + N extra ports = the
hvc0..hvc7 multi-console model) is intentionally NOT implemented here.
MULTIPORT GAP: the existing hvc_wasm path exposes 8 consoles (hvc0..hvc7,
HVC_WASM_NR); this single-port virtio-console exposes ONE. Closing that
gap (a multiport control vq + per-port add/open) is future work,
documented rather than stubbed — the host device model
(runtime/virtio/console-device.js) would grow a control vq and per-port
queues, and this registration would offer VIRTIO_CONSOLE_F_MULTIPORT.
Until then the single port is the correct, complete minimal console.

Device index follows the existing enum order (WL=0, ECHO=1, NET=2, BLK=3,
9P_ROOT=4, 9P_NIXCACHE=5), so VW_DEV_CONSOLE=6 — matching the host-side
VW_DEV_CONSOLE constants in runtime/kernel-worker.js / runtime/kernel-host.js
and the ConsoleVirtioDevice's irq = VIRTIO_WASM_IRQ_BASE(8) + 6 = 14.
(Like the 9P channels, the index assumes the preceding NET/BLK/9P slots
are built — the production config enables all of them.) Guarded by
IS_ENABLED(CONFIG_VIRTIO_CONSOLE) so the enum slot and init call are a
no-op when the stock virtio-console driver is not built.

The default 64-entry vq is fine: virtio_console moves a TTY byte stream in
small page-sized chunks (no 9P-style 128-page msize chain), so no per-id
qsize override is needed (unlike VIRTIO_ID_9P in patch 0018).

Part of issue #10 (host<->guest bridge consolidation onto virtio).
---
  drivers/virtio/virtio_wasm.c | 18 ++++++++++++++++++
  1 file changed, 18 insertions(+)

diff --git a/drivers/virtio/virtio_wasm.c b/drivers/virtio/virtio_wasm.c
index d22cd22..321ab14 100644
--- a/drivers/virtio/virtio_wasm.c
+++ b/drivers/virtio/virtio_wasm.c
@@ -377,6 +377,9 @@ enum {
 #if IS_ENABLED(CONFIG_NET_9P_VIRTIO)
 	VW_DEV_9P_ROOT,		/* virtio-9p: pc VFS export (mount tag "pcroot") */
 	VW_DEV_9P_NIXCACHE,	/* virtio-9p: nix binary cache (tag "nixcache") */
+#endif
+#if IS_ENABLED(CONFIG_VIRTIO_CONSOLE)
+	VW_DEV_CONSOLE,		/* virtio-console: a guest TTY (stock virtio_console.c) */
 #endif
 	VW_DEV_COUNT,
 };
@@ -423,6 +426,21 @@ static int __init virtio_wasm_transport_init(void)
 		pr_warn("virtio_wasm: 9p nixcache register failed: %ld\n", PTR_ERR(vw));
 #endif
 
+#if IS_ENABLED(CONFIG_VIRTIO_CONSOLE)
+	/*
+	 * virtio-console for a guest TTY (stock drivers/char/virtio_console.c).
+	 * Single port, no features: the driver binds vq[0]=receiveq (host->guest
+	 * input) + vq[1]=transmitq (guest->host output) and wires port 0 to hvc
+	 * as a console line. The host serves it via runtime/virtio/console-device.js.
+	 * Added ALONGSIDE the bespoke hvc_wasm backend (patches 0002/0003) for an
+	 * A/B during the #10 consolidation; hvc_wasm retirement is a later change.
+	 * MULTIPORT (hvc0..hvc7 parity) is a documented gap, not implemented here.
+	 */
+	vw = virtio_wasm_register(VW_DEV_CONSOLE, VIRTIO_ID_CONSOLE);
+	if (IS_ERR(vw))
+		pr_warn("virtio_wasm: console register failed: %ld\n", PTR_ERR(vw));
+#endif
+
 	return 0;
 }
 
--
